.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "September 2024" "v0.1" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RB [\| options \|]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter that replicates basic functionalities of a traditional shell.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display this help message and exit.

.SH USAGE
The shell can be used in two modes:

.TP
.B Interactive Mode
In this mode, the shell displays a prompt and waits for the user to type a command, which it then executes.

.TP
.B Non-Interactive Mode
In this mode, the shell reads and executes a command from a file or a pipeline.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B Interactive Mode:
.RS
$ ./hsh
$ ls -l
$ exit
.RE

.TP
.B Non-Interactive Mode:
.RS
$ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
.RE

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Your Name.

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1)

